@Francis

Another characteristic we share, apparently: lack of respect for national myths and the preferred, patriotic narrative 🤣. Poland's Warsaw Uprising of August-September 1944 is considered by most a heroic, worthy struggle against German occupiers. To me it was a pointless, hopeless mess, that cost the lives of 200 000 innocent people (that's not a typo - nearly a quarter of a million people died in 2 months, almost all of them civilians...) and ended with the near-total obliteration of the city. Nothing good came of it.

